-- LME Appoints Hall Commodities’ Arno Pilz to Trading Committee
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2013-11-01T11:43:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-01/lme-appoints-hall-commodities-arno-pilz-to-trading-committee.html
The London Metal Exchange named Arno Pilz, managing partner of hedge fund Hall Commodities LLP, to
its trading committee.  The appointment was registered today on the website of the
LME, the world’s biggest marketplace for industrial metals.
Pilz, who co-founded London-based Hall Commodities last year,
also serves on the exchange’s traded options committee.  The trading committee, which has 12 members from companies
including money manager BlackRock Inc. and derivatives broker
Sucden Financial Ltd., is responsible for all aspects of trading
on the LME. The panel’s next meeting is scheduled for Dec. 20,
according to the website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
